          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The total kinetic energy release in the fast",
                "neutron-induced fission of 232Th"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "J.King",
                "R.Yanez",
                "W.Loveland",
                "J.S.Barrett",
                "B.Oscar",
                "N.Fotiades",
                "F.Tovesson",
                "H.Y.Lee"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USAORU",
                "1USALAS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "J,EPJ/A,53,238,2017",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "J,EPJ/A,53,238,2017",
                    "doi": "10.1140/epja/i2017-12436-9",
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "J",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "EPJ/A",
                        "number": null,
                        "volume": "53",
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": "238"
                      },
                      "date": 2017
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "1USALAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed at Los Alamos",
                "National Laboratory- Los Alamos Neutron Science",
                "Center-Weapons Neutron Research"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "90-TH-232",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.9999
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 232Th target was comprised",
                "of a deposit of 232ThF(4) on thin carbon backing. The",
                "232Th deposit had a thickness of 195.2+-8.3 mu-g/cm2",
                "and the effective carbon backing was 120 mu-g/cm2 thick",
                "The target was tilted 45deg with respect to the",
                "incident beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two arrays of four Si PIN photodiodes were used",
                "to detect the fission products, where the photodiodes",
                "were arranged on opposite sides of the beam at angles",
                "60deg and 120deg from the incident beam. The",
                "individual PIN diodes had an area of 1 cm2, and the",
                "detectors were 2.1 cm from the center of the target.",
                "The timing pulse from a Si PIN diode coupled with the",
                "accelerator RF signal were employed to measure the",
                "time of flight of each interacting neutron. The",
                "uncertainty of the position of the photofission peak",
                "in the TOF spectrum was found to be 2.4%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron energy was determined by time of",
                "flight. The 625 mu-s macropulse proton beam contains",
                "340 micropulses of width 250 ps that are spaced 1.8",
                "mus apart, where the macropulses had a repetition",
                "rate of 100 Hz. The distance from the spallation target",
                "to the Th target was measured to be 1384.9+-1.1 cm.",
                "The 15R beam line with 13.85m flight path was used in",
                "this experiment. The 1.8 mu-s proton pulse rate",
                "theoretically allows for a small amount of",
                "wrap-around neutrons with energy < 0.4 MeV to reach",
                "the scattering chamber among the neutrons of the",
                "previous or trailing pulse. The fission cross section",
                "for 232Th(n,f) at En < .4MeV is small enough that",
                "the slow wrap-around neutrons were ignored."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron beams were generated from an",
                "unmoderated tungsten spallation source using an",
                "800MeV proton beam. Neutron time of flight and energy",
                "was calculated via the proton accelerator pulse timing."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Corrections for pulse height defects and fragment",
                "energy loss were applied"
              ]
            }
          ],
